  "text": "The Apache Kafka consumer group coordinator's state machine is implemented across multiple Java files in the group-coordinator module. The implementation includes three main group types with different state models:\n\n1. **Classic Group State Machine** (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.classic):\n   - ClassicGroupState.java defines the state enum with 5 states: EMPTY, PREPARING_REBALANCE, COMPLETING_REBALANCE, STABLE, and DEAD\n   - Each state has defined valid previous states, forming a state transition graph\n   - ClassicGroup.java implements the group class with the transitionTo() method for state transitions\n   - The classic group joins follow the join-sync-rebalance protocol:\n     * EMPTY → PREPARING_REBALANCE (when join group received)\n     * PREPARING_REBALANCE → COMPLETING_REBALANCE (when all members joined or timeout)\n     * COMPLETING_REBALANCE → STABLE (when sync group received from leader)\n     * STABLE → PREPARING_REBALANCE (on member failure, leave, or new join)\n     * All states can → DEAD (on removal)\n\n2. **Modern Consumer Group State Machine** (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.modern.consumer):\n   - ConsumerGroup.java defines ConsumerGroupState enum with states: EMPTY, ASSIGNING, RECONCILING, STABLE, DEAD\n   - Uses a different rebalance protocol based on the KIP-848 consumer group protocol\n   - Includes member-level state tracking via MemberState.java with states: STABLE, UNREVOKED_PARTITIONS, UNRELEASED_PARTITIONS\n   - CurrentAssignmentBuilder.java manages the assignment state transitions for members\n\n3. **Share Group State Machine** (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.modern.share):\n   - ShareGroup.java defines ShareGroupState enum for managed share groups\n   - Uses similar state machine patterns as consumer groups\n\n4. **Streams Group State Machine** (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.streams):\n   - StreamsGroup.java defines StreamsGroupState enum for Kafka Streams applications\n   - StreamsGroupMember.java and MemberState.java track member states\n   - Includes topology-aware assignment via TargetAssignmentBuilder.java\n\n**Key Coordinator Classes**:\n- GroupCoordinator.java: Interface defining the coordinator API for join, sync, and heartbeat operations\n- GroupCoordinatorShard.java: The replicated state machine that manages all group metadata\n- GroupMetadataManager.java: Contains handler methods classicGroupJoin(), classicGroupSync(), classicGroupHeartbeat(), and classicGroupLeave() that implement the request handling logic and state transitions\n\n**Request Flow**:\n1. JoinGroup requests are handled by classicGroupJoin() which transitions groups through PREPARING_REBALANCE\n2. SyncGroup requests are handled by classicGroupSync() which transitions from COMPLETING_REBALANCE to STABLE\n3. Heartbeat requests monitor member health and trigger rebalances if needed\n4. LeaveGroup requests managed via classicGroupLeave()\n\nThe state transitions are validated using validPreviousStates() to ensure only legal transitions occur. All state changes are recorded as CoordinatorRecords for durability and replication."
